messages.message: I also get this message when trying to get batches for my workspace, is this a bug?

Your workspace should be the same as what you see in the workspace selector -- is it a community account? community really has no concept of a workspace (or simply just call "My workspace"), workspace is an optional field so probably you can leave it blank. cc @Wilson

The error message is complaining that there's no such workspace with the name.
@Lee Is this in community context or aihub commercial? Seems like community from the error message, in which case you can leave workspace blank if you’re trying to access your personal repo (my-repo)
Yep it was that I wasn’t setting the context header on that request, so it was my fault. However the error message there didn’t help me to understand that was the issue.
This thing with the context header is really confusing for customers too, longer term it would be good to have users create different API keys so we don’t need to pass in that value
Ah good to know - agreed here. I'll make a ticket to improve the error message to help users understand the issue
